Facebbok Crawler and visualization in wordcloud

B03501044-Jeffery_Sheih

11/2/2017

library(httr)
library(jiebaRD)
library(jiebaR)
library(tm)
library(dplyr)
library(wordcloud)

txt tm package jiebaR package

#load files
filenames = list.files(getwd(),pattern = "*.txt")
files = lapply(filenames,readLines)
docs = Corpus(VectorSource(files))

#remove meaningless character
toSpace = content_transformer(function(x,pattern) {
  return (gsub(pattern," ",x))
})

docs = tm_map(docs,toSpace,"")
docs = tm_map(docs,toSpace,"")
docs = tm_map(docs,toSpace,"\\[")
docs = tm_map(docs,toSpace,"\\]")
docs = tm_map(docs,toSpace,"")
docs = tm_map(docs,toSpace,"")
docs = tm_map(docs,toSpace,"")
docs = tm_map(docs,toSpace,"")
docs = tm_map(docs,toSpace,"")
docs = tm_map(docs,toSpace,"")
docs = tm_map(docs, removePunctuation)
docs = tm_map(docs,removeNumbers)

#words cut
cutter = worker()
new_user_word(cutter,"")

tokenizer = function(x) {
  segment(x,cutter)
}

freqFrame = as.data.frame(table(unlist(lapply(docs,tokenizer)))) %>%
  arrange(desc(Freq))

#build a wordcloud
par(family=("Heiti TC Light"))
wordcloud(freqFrame$Var1,freqFrame$Freq,
          scale=c(5,0.1),min.freq=50,max.words=150,
          random.order=TRUE, random.color=FALSE,
          rot.per=.1, colors=brewer.pal(8, "Dark2"),
          ordered.colors=FALSE,use.r.layout=FALSE,
          fixed.asp=TRUE)
